#DOC source=/root/yvon/docs/briefs/lifeos-reference/26--workspaces--design-system-system.md strip=21% toon=5% net=25%
T|26 ·|0|The multi-workspace ("multi-tenant") md that lets one Mission Control run several businesses — each w/ its own theme, pages, ag, and partner logins — on a shared sb backend.
T|26 ·|1|
T|Purp|0|LifeOS is built as a multi-workspace app. Each business/project is a workspace w/ its own visual ds, page structure, workflows, and partner access, while sharing the common ag roster, memory sy, and command center. This is what makes it scale from one founder to a portfolio of companies.
T|Purp|1|
T|Work|0|Top of the sidebar: a WORKSPACE selector (active = "Vibe w/ AI") w/ chevrons to switch.
T|Work|1|Switching changes the data, the theme, and can change the available pages/workflows for that project.
T|Work|2|
T|The |0|[TABLE:4×4]
T|The |1|Each workspace has a unique, cool ds, and beyond color, each mission control per project will be designed separately — own pages, own page structure, own workflows. Some pages can be reused; some must be designed specifically per project. In the current mockups they all share the Vibe layout, but that will change.
T|The |2|
T|Mult|0|Built on sb.
T|Mult|1|Each project gets its own login. Partners receive a login that uniquely grants access to one workspace (their company's workspace only).
T|Mult|2|The owner retains the overview of all projects/workspaces, while partners are scoped to their single workspace.
T|Mult|3|This is what the visibility scoping in Brain & Wiki (Private / Team / Workspace / Cross-workspace) ties into.
T|Mult|4|
T|Why |0|It cleanly separates per-business identity and access while reusing the shared brain, ag, and command-center patterns — a true multi-tenant operating sy for a portfolio of one-person-plus-ag businesses.